The paper deals with the impact of integrity attacks on real-time pricing in smart grids, which involves the use of information and communication technologies. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category, which deals with the analysis and design of complex systems. Additionally, the paper focuses on cybersecurity threats, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The paper also uses a control-theoretic approach, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Furthermore, the paper deals with the closed loop formed by real-time price signals and price-taking demand, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category, as it deals with the impact of attacks on a key feature of smart grids that uses advanced technologies.
